EDINBURGH, SCOTLAND, UK -- The Beltane Fire Festival brings May Day to life. This festival reaches back into Celtic prehistory and peaks with a frenzy at midnight when the May Queen leads her procession around Calton Hill surrounded by 15,000 nature worshippers who have come to celebrate the return of Spring, which the May Queen brings back to life. This image is available for publication. You can see more at my web site www.jimrichardsonphotography.com

EDINBURGH, SCOTLAND, UK -- The Beltain Fire Festival brings May Day to life. This festival reaches back into Celtic prehistory and peaks with a frenzy at midnight when the May Queen leads her procession around Calton Hill surrounded by 15,000 nature worshippers who have come to celebrate the return of Spring, which the May Queen brings back to life. For lighting fans: lighting was a matter of balancing the existing light from the torches with the flash on an off camera cord. I waited until the May Queen was in the shadows so just the flash would light her up. Wild night with 15,000 people in the darkness of Calton Hill in Edinburgh. Trying to get into position was struggle enough, let alone being ready to light the scene when I got there. This image is available for publication. You can see more at my web site www.jimrichardsonphotography.com

There were two Chilean groups high-up in opposite stands to the left and right of us. They cheered their hearts out when their Band came on. BBC highlight video.
